	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Hmm the 2nd one does sound really good. But I mean playing Sonic2 it sounded off without the cap, like the ring and jump sounds. The new circuit I made did sound way better then the crummy built in one tho.
<br />
<br />Now for the SNES, you shouldn't leave the filter out. Its called a reconstruction filter, and is part of the DACs operation. 
<br />
<br />The most you will get is 16kHz of sound, everything higher will be aliasing noise. So make a nice quality 16kHz 2nd order filter, and you will keep all the good sounds!

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


